<br>
“<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>By Prexus!!</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->” he cursed rushing to gather the airborn records. It was then he heard the city alarm… there was an intruder! Clutching the papers to his chest, he froze, feeling the presence of another. Spinning around quickly he faced a room filled to the ceiling with books and records. <br>
<br>
Here housed the entire history of Norrath, family trees, legends of great, noble and simpleman alike. Kvael closed his eyes and inhaled the scent of ancient scrolls and bound tomes, feeling a brief sense of safety, security.<br>
<br>
“ Keeper Rhi’shi… Kvael?” a pained femme voice asked from the shadows, sending the Erudite into a panic, dropping his papers, grabbing a nearby candlestick. <br>
<br>
In a reed-piped voice Kvael yelled at the shadow “ Who goes there?!”<br>
<br>
While staring at the tall bookshelf, the books started to distort and shimmer… a cloak of invisibility was fading from a black robed figure. Kvael took a defensive step back as the image cleared. No, the cloak wasn’t black, but charred and torn. The figure lifted it’s head, letting the hood fall back.<br>
<br>
With a loud clang, the candlestick hit the marble floor as Kvael shrieked in horror. Standing before him was a femme Erudite, emaciated, scarred and burned almost beyond mortal form. The figure wavered slightly, then fell into Kvael’s arms. It was all he could do to hold her upright, the stench of death was so powerful.<br>
<br>
Guiding her to the floor, Kvael said “ Child!! You need a healer… let me…”<br>
<br>
His words where cut off quickly as the stranger’s hand shot up to grip his throat. She hissed, “ No… no healers. Just take my bag.” She slid the bag from her shoulder, letting in lay on the floor beside her. <br>
<br>
“Who attacked you… the intruder?!” Kvael stood up quickly, heading for the door. <br>
<br>
Suddenly, an arch of magical power crackled through the air, gripping the Librarian, sending his body into a terrible seizure, draining his life and restoring it to the stranger on the floor. <br>
<br>
The femme quickly stood up and went over to his side, guiding him to the floor now, whispering: “ Do NOT summon a healer, nor guards. I am sorry but I NEED you to listen to me!!” <br>
<br>
He looked up into the familiar face of the beauty before him, Erudite caramel skin, bright green eyes staring at him in panicked desperation. Suddenly, it was all clear. <br>
<br>
“ You!!” he said, “ Shai’le, it IS you... but but... child why…?” The pain he felt was so great that it sent him into unconsciousness. <br>
<br>
After what seemed like hours, but was only a few minutes, Kvael awoke with a start. He was still lying on the floor, and near him was the orphan child he used to catch hiding in the cellars of the Library, pouring over books instead of playing with the others. <br>
<br>
Now she was this beautiful stranger, seated in meditative form. A chill rushed over him as he realized she was a practicer of the black arts, a Necromancer. In the background, the city was still on full alert. Considering his options, he decided screaming would be the fastest way, instead of moving in his weakened state. <br>
<br>
As he filled his lungs with air, and he screamed &quot; GUARDS!!!&quot; <br>
<br>
Shai'le's eyes flashed open, filled with tears. “ Please…” was all she said. She grabbed her bag and handed it to him.<br>
<br>
Just then the doors of the Library flew open, guards pouring into the building, surrounding her, the commander striding in confidently, behind his men.<br>
<br>
“ Heretic!” he spat. As she began to chat and her fingertips came to light with magic, an enchanter stepped in and mesmerized her. Her body and her magic froze, leaving her completely invulnerable, tremoring only when the enchanters sieved magic from her. <br>
<br>
“ Shai’le, we drove you out before and what a mistake,” he moved in to face her “ …we should have killed you.” <br>
<br>
“ Do not call me that name!”, as she spoke the room filled with gasps. “ I am Malaele d’Aeliu, Daughter of Malaeliu, banished Priestess of Innoruuk.” <br>
<br>
The commander cut in, “ Look at your skin, Shai’le… it is NOT blue! You are not elven! You are ERUDITE! Why would you claim blood of a Teir'dal. You ARE insane!!”<br>
<br>
“ Your mighty guards of Prexus” she spat back “ didn’t protect me from being abducted as a child! Nor did they ever come to find me!” <br>
<br>
Silence filled the room, as Kvael stood up to peer closer. She continues, “ No, Malaeliu wasn’t my mother at birth, but she saved me and other children… my sisters! And after her death?! Did Quellious give me the coppers I had to beg for? Did your precious Prexus guide me back here to your vile cursed forest?”.<br>
<br>
The commander stepped forward, drew his long two-handed sword and cut the woman down. Freed from the enchanter’s spell, Malaele channeled her magic into the commander to restore her health from his. But, completely drained, all she could do was lie in the floor, bleeding to death.<br>
<br>
“ We should have destroyed you when we found you! No one can live with evil and not be effected. Now you grow up to make us proud, the vile Bonecaster!”.<br>
<br>
She shot back, in desparation “ You gave me no choice, throwing me out in the forests with no training… how else was I to survive? I had to feed off the lives of the forest creatures. I cared not where my power was from, Quellious, Prexus or Cazic Thule.” <br>
<br>
The crowd gasped and murmured… “ Heresy” as they pulled her to her feet.<br>
<br>
She continued in the ancient Combine tongue, knowing Kvael would understand… “ I wanted to unite my family, and piece my Mother’s story together. Now you have it, do not let it die with me, please I beg you…”<br>
<br>
Cold blue steel cut off the last of her words. The commander withdrew his sword from the girl, wiping her blood on her black robe. “ Dispose of this in the usual Heretic manner.”<br>
